               <msContents>
                  <summary>This very mutilated papyrus preserves the beginning of a document directed to a logistes Phoibammon of the Oxyrhynchite nome by two persons. They complain about the behaviour of a certain Aurelius Aion of their village who had them imprisoned on false accusations of theft.</summary>
